      description     : "EX19-MB-000135 - Exchange internal receive connectors must not allow anonymous connections."
      info            : "This control is used to limit the servers that may use this server as a relay. If a Simple Mail Transport Protocol (SMTP) sender does not have a direct connection to the internet (for example, an application that produces reports to be emailed), it will need to use an SMTP Receive connector that does have a path to the internet (for example, a local email server) as a relay.

